<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.893966>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 13. Cryptopygus tingus sp. nov.: 1, dorsal sensilla and macrochaetae of th. II to abd. V – VI (other seta omitted); 2, chaetotaxy of abdominal segments IV and V – VI, dorsal view, with detail of abd. V – VI: smooth oval sensillum; 3, postantennal organ and its surrounding seta; 4, ant. segment I, ventral view; 5, ant. segments II, III and IV, dorsal view; 6, sensilla of ant. segment IV (common seta omitted), dorsal view; 7, left labial palp; 8, femur and tibiotarsus of leg III, lateral view; 9, ventral tube, lateral view; 10, tenaculum; 11, manubrium, anterior view, right dens anterior and left dens posterior view; 12, mucro; 13, male genital opening and its surrounding seta." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/893966/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

